items.name: Konoko (Oni game)
items.description:
Lora model of Konoko from Oni game. Not sure if people here are old enough to know, but it was a cool game from 2001 by Bungie.

This model was trained on only 6 images - I was trying to challenge myself and do my best with what I had. Obviously quality is not equal with what I usually post, but after a lot of work I think I got to the point where it's ok and strikes some balance between being somewhat flexible and still lookign about right. The text on breastplate was a lost cause through because of flip augmentation.

Full prompt is konoko, shoulder armor, armor, bodysuit, breastplate, clothes writing, fingerless gloves, knee pads, boots. Sometimes removing armor actually gives better results. Also torn bodysuit works quite well so you can try konoko, bodysuit, torn bodysuit. Works pretty good with other clothes or nude, although often insists on earrings and is hard to persuade it to drop it.

Also bodysuit comes out better better if you add highleg, leotard, thighhighs to negatives, otherwise it often shows bare thighs.

items.name: Tash Oakley
items.description:
I thought Devin would miss her best friend, so here she is...

Natasha 'Tash' Oakley is an Australian model and social media celebrity, with more than 3M followers on Instagram as of today.

This is step 170 of a 250-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (tash0akley:0.99), a woman as a movie star, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"

items.name: Ciri | The Witcher 3 : Wild Hunt
items.description:
Character Lora of Ciri from The Witcher 3 : Wild Hunt

"Yield and save me some time!" -Ciri

A princess, time-traveler and honorary witcher walk into a bar -soul3142


This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives 4.0 International License.

If you want to, you can support me on Patreon or Buy me Coffee.

My Witcher LoRA Index - soul3142's Guide to the Witcher Universe. additionally you can check out some characters i've made from other games also.

Main Trigger Word - ciriW3_soul3142 , check examples for other ones.

RECOMMENDATIONS :-

  1. Highres Fix - must, if you are getting blurry and ugly images

    My upscale method: txt2img 512x768 -> send to img2img -> controlnet tile upscale, tile diffusion 2x scale with 4xUltrasharp upscaler and tiled vae

  2. Weight: 0.6 - 0.8

  3. Clip Skip: 2

  4. Denoising - Don't go too high, it can alter a lot of details

  5. For better face's - you can use ADetailer

I use 0.7 weight, 25 steps, Euler a, Clip skip 2 in nearly all my examples with almost same, simple +ve/-ve prompts regardless of checkpoint for my own consistency purposes.

There are imperfections here & there, which i usually leave it in as is, (i never do any inpainting in examples), most of which like hands can be fixed with better prompting, negative embeddings while other like weapons are just bad majority of the time no matter the model as of today.

Some LoRA's are flexible with any clothing, some are not (usually character's with single costume) so keep these things in mind.

This is an unofficial fanmade LoRA, not intended for any commercial purpose and use. All characters and IP rights are owned by their respective creators and owners. I do not own rights to any of these characters.

items.name: John Smith from "The Man in the High Castle" (2015)
items.description:
After 158 models, 243 followers, 28K downloads, thanks to the 9 supporters who made it possible.

The Man in the High Castle is a television series that ran from November 2015 to November 2019. It is based on the 1962 novel of the same name by American science fiction author Philip K. Dick.

The story is set in an alternate history of the world in which the Axis powers won World War II. The United States and Canada have been partitioned into three sections - The Japanese puppet state known as the Japanese Pacific States, which comprise the former United States west of the Rocky Mountains, a Nazi puppet state known as Nazi America that comprises the eastern half, and a Neutral Zone that acts as a buffer between the two.

Reichsführer John Smith (October 14, 1914 - ca. 1965) was a former U.S Army Captain who joined the SS following the surrender of the United States. He quickly rose through the ranks to Obergruppenführer, and was assigned to investigate the American Resistance in New York.

items.name: Barrier Reef Colours
items.description:
This model was trained on 19th Century prints of the corals, sponges, and fish of Australia's Great Barrier Reef. These prints were the work of pioneering marine biologist William Saville-Kent, who used a custom-built tripod and specialised filters to photograph marine life from above the water's surface with primitive camera equipment. Saville-Kent used these photographs as the basis for beautiful colour illustrations that captured the vibrant colours and patterns of tropical marine life.

This model reproduces the smooth textures, rich detail, and vivid colours of the original prints.
